<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Finding the Needle in the Logs on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/</link><description>Recent content in Finding the Needle in the Logs on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>1. Scenario 1 — Log-First Triage</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/1-introduction/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/1-introduction/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In many real-world incidents, the first signal is an alert or a report from a user — not a trace or a dashboard. The responder opens their logging tool and starts investigating. This is the &lt;strong&gt;log-first&lt;/strong&gt; approach, and it&amp;rsquo;s how this scenario works.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unlike a sequential RUM → APM → Logs path where you arrive at logs with context already established, here you start with a blank slate in Log Observer. No prior trace context. No service map. Just logs and your investigative skills.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. Navigate to Log Observer</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/2-navigate-log-observer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/2-navigate-log-observer/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;From the main navigation menu in Splunk Observability Cloud, click on &lt;strong&gt;Log Observer&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the time range to &lt;strong&gt;Last 15 minutes&lt;/strong&gt; using the time picker in the top-right corner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the filter bar, add a filter for your workshop environment:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Add Filter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;code&gt;deployment.environment&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set the value to the environment name provided by your instructor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;!-- TODO screenshot: Log Observer landing page with time range and environment filter set --&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should now see the Log Observer landing page with two main areas:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. Filtering and Grouping</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/3-filtering-and-grouping/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/3-filtering-and-grouping/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;With Log Observer open and your environment filter set, you&amp;rsquo;re looking at all logs from all services. That&amp;rsquo;s a lot of noise. Let&amp;rsquo;s narrow it down.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 1: Group by Severity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on the &lt;strong&gt;Group By&lt;/strong&gt; drop-down box &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use the search to find and select &lt;code&gt;severity&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click the &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; button.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Notice that the timeline chart legend now shows the distribution of log levels — &lt;strong&gt;debug&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;info&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;warn&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;error&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>4. Timeline and Patterns</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/4-timeline-and-patterns/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/4-timeline-and-patterns/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ve narrowed down to error logs from a single service. Now let&amp;rsquo;s understand &lt;em&gt;when&lt;/em&gt; the problem started and &lt;em&gt;what&lt;/em&gt; the errors look like.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Step 1: Analyze the Timeline&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Look at the timeline chart at the top of the page. Focus on the shape of the error bars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-2" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-2" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-3" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-3" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-4" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-4" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-5" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-5" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-6" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-6" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-7" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-7" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-8" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-8" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-9" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-9" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-0" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Is the error rate constant, or did it spike at a specific time? What might that tell you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-1" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-1" hidden data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;A sudden spike suggests a deployment, configuration change, or external dependency failure at that point in time. A constant error rate suggests the issue has been present since the service started. Both patterns are clues to the root cause.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-2" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-2" hidden data-tab-label="Question"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do all the error logs share the same message pattern, or are there multiple distinct errors?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--panel-3" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-4-timeline-and-patterns-md-1-1--tab-3" hidden data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;&lt;!-- TODO: Update with actual patterns from OTel Demo v2.0.1 --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Look for repeating message templates. If all errors share the same pattern, you likely have a single root cause. Multiple patterns may indicate cascading failures.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>5. Identify the Root Cause</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/5-root-cause/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/5-root-cause/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ve filtered to the right service, analyzed the timeline, and examined the error patterns. Time to identify the root cause.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--success"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Click on an error entry in the log table to open the detail pane.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Read the &lt;code&gt;message&lt;/code&gt; field carefully.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-2" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-2" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-3" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-3" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-4" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-4" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;Question&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-5" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-5" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;Answer&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-0" data-tab-label="Question"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based on the error message, what is the root cause? What would you recommend to the development team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--panel-1" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-en-splunk4rookies-o11y-rookies-26-1-modules-6-logs-5-root-cause-md-1-1--tab-1" hidden data-tab-label="Answer"&gt;&lt;!-- TODO: Update with actual root cause from OTel Demo v2.0.1 fault injection --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error message reveals the specific failure. Based on this, you would recommend the development team investigate the failing component — whether it&amp;rsquo;s an invalid configuration, an expired credential, a missing dependency, or a code defect.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>6. Scenario 2 — TBD</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/6-scenario-2-overview/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/6-scenario-2-overview/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--warning"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Under Development&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;This scenario is under development. The content below is a placeholder.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2 id="candidate-scenarios"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;Candidate Scenarios&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#candidate-scenarios" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Two directions are being considered for this second scenario:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option A: Error Spike Investigation&lt;/strong&gt;
An error spike appears in a specific time window. You must use Log Observer to identify when it started, which services are affected, and correlate with deployment events to determine what changed.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>7. Scenario 2 — Steps</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/7-scenario-2-placeholder/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/en/splunk4rookies/o11y-rookies-26/1-modules/6-logs/7-scenario-2-placeholder/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--warning"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Under Development&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;This page is a placeholder. Exercise steps will be added once the scenario is finalized.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
